=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Recorder_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright noisy sound, with noise oscillator character around 62 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: noisy
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 61.9138
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.1265
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0233
  pitch_clarity: 1.5298
  inharmonicity: 0.0027
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -24.3556
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Recorder Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Recorder.html
// Tags: Recorder, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
r = Recorder(s);
{ GVerb.ar(Dust.ar(4)) }.play; // play on bus 64
r.record(numChannels: 2);
r.stopRecording;
